{
  "page": "Ulthos",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/ff/Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg/400px-Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"267\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/ff/Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg/600px-Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/ff/Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg/800px-Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Locator_map_Ulthos_in_Known_world.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Location of Ulthos in the <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">known world</a></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Ulthos</b> is a landmass in the far east of the <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">known world</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Geography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Geography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Geography\">Geography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ulthos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Geography\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ulthos lies south of <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai\" title=\"Asshai\">Asshai</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Shadow_Lands\" title=\"Shadow Lands\">Shadow Lands</a> of eastern <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>, with the <a href=\"/index.php/Saffron_Straits\" title=\"Saffron Straits\">Saffron Straits</a> separating the landmasses. Several isles, including <a href=\"/index.php/Ulos\" title=\"Ulos\">Ulos</a>, are situated in these straits.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafthe_east.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafthe_east.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Sothoryos\" title=\"Sothoryos\">Sothoryos</a> is west of Ulthos across the <a href=\"/index.php/Jade_Sea\" title=\"Jade Sea\">Jade Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafthe_known_world.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafthe_known_world.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Little is known about Ulthos,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafother_lands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafother_lands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> with some considering it a continent like <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> and others reporting it to be a large island.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafulthos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafulthos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> According to cartographer Jonathan Roberts, illustrator of <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Lands_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"The Lands of Ice and Fire\">The Lands of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Ulthos has a purple-black jungle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> An unnamed river with at least one tributary runs through the jungle of northwestern Ulthos.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafthe_east.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafthe_east.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ulthos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Merchants have dreamed of reaching Ulthos and <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai\" title=\"Asshai\">Asshai</a> by sailing west from <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Elissa_Farman\" title=\"Elissa Farman\">Elissa Farman</a> believed there were other lands and seas located between Westeros and the far eastern shores of Ulthos and <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ulthos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Sadly, the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a>'s knowledge grows thinner the farther we travel from the lands that the men of the east call the <a href=\"/index.php/Sunset_Kingdoms\" title=\"Sunset Kingdoms\">Sunset Kingdoms</a>, for congress with the more distant realms of <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a> has ever been sparse. We know even less about the southern reaches of <a href=\"/index.php/Sothoryos\" title=\"Sothoryos\">Sothoryos</a> and far Ulthos, and nothing at all about whatever lands may lie beyond the <a href=\"/index.php/Last_Light\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Last Light\">Last Light</a> and across the <a href=\"/index.php/Sunset_Sea\" title=\"Sunset Sea\">Sunset Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafother_lands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafother_lands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ulthos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>, the ambiguity over whether Ulthos is a separate continent or a big island off <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a> highlights how people from <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> do not know much about the <a href=\"/index.php/Further_East\" title=\"Further East\">Further East</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Ulthos might be a reference to <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thule\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Thule\">Ultima Thule</a></i>, a name used on ancient and medieval maps to signify barely-known lands at the edge of charts. <i>Ultima Thule</i> is Latin for \"Farthest Thule\", and Ulthos is the farthest land that is known to people of Westeros.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ulthos&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtloiafthe_east.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtloiafthe_east.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtloiafthe_east.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Lands_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"The Lands of Ice and Fire\">The Lands of Ice and Fire</a></i>, The East.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtloiafthe_known_world.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtloiafthe_known_world.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Lands_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"The Lands of Ice and Fire\">The Lands of Ice and Fire</a></i>, The Known World.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafother_lands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafother_lands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafother_lands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Other Lands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafulthos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafulthos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Ulthos.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Fantastic Maps: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fantasticmaps.com/2013/03/the-east/\">The East</a> (March 22, 2013)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Jaehaerys and Alysanne - Their Triumphs and Tragedies.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Vulture: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.vulture.com/2014/11/george-rr-martin-new-book.html\">George R.R. Martin on What Not to Believe in Game of Thrones</a> (November 6, 2014)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" 